  "raw_text": "track B at point X in time was not to help me or any other single given person, but to depose + destroy the \"cont\" t Spirators.\" Well, this broad historic purpose was achieved, but there were loose ends. My error has been to regard the tracks as totally different each from the others. Okay, I was a portion of the changed part when the tinkering took place at point X I obtained new memories + a different history + hence different personality. But the situation \"at the other end,\" which is to say, the section out of which the Xerox Missive emanated wasn't changed. The missive was sent. The track B PKD couldn't have handled it - wouldn't have known 1) wWhat it was (signified) or 2) what to do with it. Such fuckups must abound when part of a world is changed with other parts left unchanged; you get spooky \"doesn't compute\" (apply any longer) phenomena. So, I'm saying, Thomas had to be brought back (at least temporarily) or there'd This weird loose-end Xerox object. be what I got to see was: the ghostly outlines of the iron prison world of track A, + the Logos weaver - reweaver savior, actually at work. (I was temporarily \"above\" worlds, abore both tracks. I was in the reweaver's world, not ours 90 (cf \"adjustment Team\"). That Xerox must have really been Lethal to requires a temporary return of the me of track A, Anyhow it worked, + the me (Thomas) of track A handled it fine. en It contained - not just information - but coded command - instructions - which Thomas was on the look out for. He knew the exact day it'd come. You don't suppose \"Tears\" depicts a Russian (i.e. CP). dominated us. (+ accurately describes track A?)? I doubt it - it was more an anti-cp police state But- Romans. Could it have been an alternate world in which the Roman Empire never fell + never embraced a con‐ version to Christianity? i.e. modern Romans? In which case the intervention may have occured (i.e. point X) in apostolic times (as scripture promised). Our world, track By is better than A, but the plan is not complete; when it as complete we will have track C Anyhow all this accounts for me having such an unuseral experience (anamnesis about track A, + seeing the weaven/ weaven) when no one else (or few else) remember: the fucking Xerox missive was a serious - even tethal-dangling \"bit\" of track A; + I see this suddenly: it must have been essential to either the efficacy of track B +/or the maintenance of obliviousness to + abolition of track A that the Xerox missive be handled right. Had it been handled wrong 70 would not have been [merely] a disaster for me, but rather a damage - maybe even disaster - to the succe ness of replacing A with B. issful‐ In fact the successful handling of the Xerox miss he was not merely necessary to the success of track B but must have been part of the replacement by B of A itself. So We wind up with the curiosity that the establishment of B (+ no one remembering A) necessitated a temporary very localized restoration of a bit of A (as if all of A hal been phased out too completely or too soon). The Xerox missive, then constituted a bit of anomie within the track B cosmos + could only be inteprated by a restoration of its other part: i.e. Thomas restored to receive it. How does this fit in with the apostolic Xtians drawing the DNa molecule (+ knowing about gene‐ pool memory) + climbing up the garden hose of time like a snake\"? It is this (+ really something): those authentic Xtians are using their knowledge + related abilities to travel back + forth (\"Garden-hose‐ wise) through linear time for the purpose of altering controlling) history; thus it is they, as extensors of 2 ZebRa, who are doing the tinkering, producing one alternate world after another, + each new one The true, secret Xtian church KW + I better. posited are able to reweave reality through a strange form of time-travel. But this points to Thomas as coming from 2000 years ago. Still, I am sure of the above e the \"Garden hose\" +